result.execSummary:
Zenitra Zaphorah Forester was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Zenitra Zaphorah Forester was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: copy of criminal complaint and waiver of extradition mailed to Governor's office.
This did not take place. Court event needs to be in court record to dispose of case.

9:31 AM Defendant Zenitra Zaphorah Forester appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Joseph M. Schieffer in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant wishes to proceed with assistance from the PD. Court goes over Def's right to have an attorney. Defendant understands. Court explains extradition process. Def wishes to return to Scott County MN and waives extradition. Defendant signs waiver of extradition. Court will sign waiver of extradition when presented. Def requests to be released and return to Scott County voluntarily. Court: warrant was issued. Def understands. 9:40
